{
  "texts": [
    "In this analogy, the bosonic bath represents the localized spins, while the spontaneously emitted excitation corresponds to the magnon propagating through the spin chain.",
    "The two relevant electronic levels are the excited state |e⟩ and the ground state |g⟩.For such a situation, standard approximations (see App.",
    "B) yield a Markovian behavior and hence an ex- (a), (b): Logarithm of the electronic quasimomentum distribution n k (t) as a function of time for a small (J/t0 = 0.9) and a large (J/t0 = 3.0) Kondo coupling, respectively.",
    "After a fast initial dynamics, n k (t) exhibits two well-defined peaks at k = -π/2 + J/4, and k = π/2 -J/4 for the case of (a).",
    "These finite-momentum peaks are inconsistent with a thermal state in the steady-state regime."
  ]
}